<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Merry</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-17"><hi rend="italic">September 17,
                                    1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In the name of President Roosevelt and the American nation you will
                            assure President Iglesias of deep appreciation of his messages of
                            solicitude and sympathy in the hour of suspense and affliction.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>